&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE ROTHERHAM NHS FOUNDATION TRUST&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THERAPY SUPPORT WORKER – BAND 3&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full time 37.5hrs – Fixed term Contract until 31st May 2021&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;COMMUNITY THERAPY TEAM  &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic therapy support worker to join our exciting Community Therapy Team within Rotherham NHS Foundation Trust.  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role involves working within the Community Therapy Team who in-reaches into Rotherham Hospital emergency department, assessing and treating patients to prevent hospital admissions and facilitate early supported discharge. This is linked to the pathways which includes Integrated Urgent Response at Home and Integrated Rehabilitation &amp; Reablement at Home. There will be an expectation of flexibility to work throughout the community therapy team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will join a team of existing therapy support workers in our well established service.  You will support the physiotherapists and occupational therapists in providing assessment, rehabilitation and crisis management in the patient’s own home. This will include carrying, transporting and issuing equipment, following rehab/exercise plans and practising mobility. The team includes physiotherapists, occupational therapists and therapy support workers and works closely with a wider MDT of nurses, nursing support workers, social workers, voluntary sector and care staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team provides a 7 day service and there will be an expectation to work weekends. The work pattern is negotiable, but we wouold like you to work 4 longer days. (Weekend shifts has enhancement pay attached).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should ideally be experienced in community working and rehabilitation and be an excellent team worker and be able to demonstrate good communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a strong commitment to supervision, PDR and staff training. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recent experience of community work in a NHS/Care setting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full driving license with access to a vehicle for business use&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Valid work permit or be eligible to work within the UK&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is subject to Occupational Health Screening and Criminal Records Bureau Disclosure checking.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Claire Hill - Community Therapy Team leader  mob: 07733314614 or&lt;/p&gt;
